# Scope: mobile app only (website frozen)

As of 2026-07-16 the **website is out of scope**. Do not change Next.js UI/pages until the user explicitly lifts this freeze.

## In scope
- `mobile/` (Expo / React Native app) — primary product
- Shared backend only when the app needs it: `app/api/**`, `lib/**` (outside `mobile/`), `supabase/**`

## Out of scope (do not touch)
- Website UI/pages: `app/**/page.tsx`, `app/**/layout.tsx` (except API routes), `components/**` used by the Next.js site
- Website-only styling, nav, or feature work “for parity”

## Examples
- ❌ Adding a Google Tasks panel to `app/tasks/page.tsx`
- ✅ Sync + API under `app/api/**` + UI in `mobile/app/(tabs)/tasks.tsx`
- ✅ Migration in `supabase/` consumed by the mobile app

If a request is ambiguous, assume **mobile only**. Backend changes are allowed solely to serve the app.
